  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Commission to Joshua"
      title: "God\u2019s Commission to Joshua"
      number: 1
      content: "  Now it happened after the death of Moses the servant of the Lord,
        that the Lord spoke to Joshua the son of Nun, Moses\u2019 servant (attendant),
        saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CMoses My servant is dead; now therefore arise [to take his
        place], cross over this Jordan, you and all this people, into the land which
        I am giving to them, to the sons of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I have given you every place on which the sole of your foot treads,
        just as I promised to Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'From the wilderness [of Arabia in the south] and this Lebanon [in
        the north], even as far as the great river, the river Euphrates [in the east],
        all the land of the Hittites (Canaan), and as far as the Great [Mediterranean]
        Sea toward the west shall be your territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'No man will [be able to] stand before you [to oppose you] as long
        as you live. Just as I was [present] with Moses, so will I be with you; I
        will not fail you or abandon you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Be strong and confident and courageous, for you will give this people
        as an inheritance the land which I swore to their fathers (ancestors) to
        give them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Only be strong and very courageous; be careful to do [everything]
        in accordance with the entire law which Moses My servant commanded you; do
        not turn from it to the right or to the left, so that you may prosper and
        be successful wherever you go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'This Book of the Law shall not depart from your mouth, but you shall
        read [and meditate on] it day and night, so that you may be careful to do
        [everything] in accordance with all that is written in it; for then you will
        make your way prosperous, and then you will be successful. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Joshua Assumes Command'
      title: Joshua Assumes Command
      number: 9
      content: "Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous! Do not be terrified
        or dismayed (intimidated), for the Lord your God is with you wherever you
        go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Joshua commanded the officers of the people, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CGo throughout the camp and command the people, saying, \u2018Prepare
        your provisions, for within three days you are to cross this [river] Jordan,
        to go in to take possession of the land which the Lord your God is giving
        you to possess [as an inheritance].\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'To the Reubenites and to the Gadites and to the half-tribe of Manasseh,
        Joshua said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CRemember the word which Moses the servant of the Lord commanded
        you, saying, \u2018The Lord your God is giving you rest (peace) and will
        give you this land [east of the Jordan].\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your wives, your children, and your cattle shall [be allowed to]
        stay in the land which Moses gave you on this [eastern] side of the Jordan,
        but you shall go across [the river] before your brothers (the other tribes)
        armed for battle, all your brave warriors, and you shall help them [conquer
        and take possession of their land], '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "until the Lord gives your brothers rest, as He has given you, and
        they also take possession of the land which the Lord your God is giving them.
        Then you shall [be allowed to] return to your own land, and take possession
        of that which Moses the servant of the Lord gave you beyond the Jordan toward
        the sunrise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  They answered Joshua, saying, \u201CAll that you have commanded
        us we will do, and wherever you send us we will go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Just as we obeyed Moses in all things, so will we obey you; only
        may the Lord your God be with you as He was with Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Any man who rebels against your command and does not obey everything
        that you command him, shall be put to death; only be strong and courageous.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rahab Shelters Spies'
      title: Rahab Shelters Spies
      number: 1
      content: "  Joshua the son of Nun sent two men as scouts secretly from Shittim,
        saying, \u201CGo, view the land, especially Jericho [the walled city].\u201D
        So they went and came to the house of a prostitute named Rahab, and lodged
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now the king of Jericho was told, \u201CBehold, men from the sons
        of Israel have come here tonight to spy and search out the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So the king of Jericho sent word to Rahab, saying, \u201CBring out
        the men who have come to you, who entered your house, because they have come
        [as spies] to search out all the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the woman had taken the two men and hidden them; so she said,
        \u201CYes, two men came to me, but I did not know where they were from. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When it was time to close the [city] gate at dark, the men left;
        I do not know where they went. Pursue them quickly, for [if you do] you will
        overtake them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But [in fact] she had brought the scouts up to the roof and had hidden
        them under the stalks of flax which she had laid in order on the roof [to
        dry]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the [king\u2019s] men pursued them on the road to the Jordan as
        far as the fords [east of Jericho]; as soon as the pursuers had gone out
        after them, the gate [of the city] was shut.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now before the two men lay down [to sleep], Rahab came up to them
        on the roof, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and she said to the men, \u201CI know that the Lord has given you
        the land, and that the terror and dread of you has fallen on us, and that
        all the inhabitants of the land have melted [in despair] because of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For we have heard how the Lord dried up the water of the Red Sea
        for you when you came out of Egypt, and what you did to the two kings of
        the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan [on the east], to Sihon and Og, whom
        you utterly destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When we heard it, our hearts melted [in despair], and a [fighting]
        spirit no longer remained in any man because of you; for the Lord your God,
        He is God in heaven above and on earth beneath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And now, please swear [an oath] to me by the Lord, since I have shown
        you kindness, that you also will show kindness to my father\u2019s household
        (family), and give me a pledge of truth and faithfulness, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and spare my father and my mother and my brothers and my sisters,
        along with everyone who belongs to them, and let us all live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Promise to Rahab'
      title: The Promise to Rahab
      number: 14
      content: "So the men said to her, \u201COur lives for yours if you do not tell
        [anyone about] this business of ours; then when the Lord gives us the land
        we will show you kindness and faithfulness [and keep our agreement with you].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then she let them down by a rope through the window, for her house
        was built into the city wall, so that she was living on the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And she said to them, \u201CGo [west] to the hill country, so that
        the pursuers [who have headed east] will not encounter you; hide yourselves
        there for three days until the pursuers return. Then afterward you can go
        your way.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The men said to her, \u201CWe shall be blameless and free from this
        oath which you have made us swear, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "unless, when we come into the land, you tie this cord of scarlet
        thread in the window through which you let us down, and bring into the house
        your father and your mother and your brothers and all your father\u2019s
        household [so that they will be safe]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But if anyone goes out the doors of your house into the street, his
        blood shall be on his own head [that is, his own responsibility], and we
        shall be blameless and free [from our oath]; however, if a hand is laid on
        anyone who is with you in the house, his blood shall be on our head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But if you tell [anyone] this business of ours, we shall be blameless
        and free from the oath which you made us swear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "She said, \u201CAccording to your words, so be it.\u201D Then Rahab
        sent them off, and they departed; and she tied the scarlet cord in the window.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They left and went [on their way] to the hill country [west of Jericho],
        and stayed there [hidden in the caves] three days until the pursuers returned.
        The pursuers had searched all along the road but had not found them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the two men turned back and came down from the hill country
        and crossed over [the Jordan] and came to Joshua the son of Nun [at Shittim],
        and told him everything that had happened to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They said to Joshua, \u201CCertainly the Lord has given all the land
        into our hands; for all the inhabitants of the land have melted [in despair]
        because of us.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Crosses the Jordan'
      title: Israel Crosses the Jordan
      number: 1
      content: '  Joshua got up early in the morning; then he and all the children
        of Israel set out from Shittim and came to the Jordan, and they spent the
        night there before they crossed [the river]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it happened at the end of three days that the officers went throughout
        the camp, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and they commanded the people, \u201CWhen you see the ark of the
        covenant of the Lord your God being carried by the Levitical priests, then
        you shall set out from where you are and follow it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "However, there shall be a distance between you and it of about 2,000
        cubits (3,000 ft.) by measurement. Do not come near it, so that you may [be
        able to see the ark and] know the way you are to go, for you have not passed
        this way before.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Joshua said to the people, \u201CSanctify yourselves [for His
        purpose], for tomorrow the Lord will do wonders (miracles) among you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Joshua said to the priests, \u201CTake up the ark of the covenant
        and cross over [the river] ahead of the people.\u201D So they took up the
        ark of the covenant and went on ahead of the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Lord said to Joshua, \u201CThis day I will begin to magnify and
        exalt you in the sight of all Israel, so that they may know that just as
        I was with Moses, I will [also] be with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "You shall command the priests who carry the ark of the covenant,
        saying, \u2018When you come to the edge of the waters of the Jordan, you
        shall stand still in the Jordan.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Joshua said to the Israelites, \u201CCome here, and listen to the
        words of the Lord your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Joshua said, \u201CBy this you shall know that the living God is
        among you, and that He will, without fail, drive out from before you the
        Canaanite, the Hittite, the Hivite, the Perizzite, the Girgashite, the Amorite,
        and the Jebusite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, the ark of the covenant of the Lord of all the earth is crossing
        over ahead of you [leading the way] into the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So now take for yourselves twelve men from the tribes of Israel,
        one man from each tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When the soles of the feet of the priests who carry the ark of the
        Lord, the Lord of all the earth, [come to] rest in the waters of the Jordan,
        the waters of the Jordan flowing down from above will be cut off, and they
        will stand in one mass [of water].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So when the people set out from their tents to cross over the Jordan
        with the priests who were carrying the ark of the covenant before the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and when those who were carrying the ark came up to the Jordan, and
        the feet of the priests carrying the ark were submerged at the edge of the
        water (for the Jordan overflows all of its banks throughout the time of harvest), '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the waters which were flowing down from above stopped and rose up
        in one mass a great distance away at Adam, the city that is beside Zarethan.
        Those [waters] flowing downward toward the sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea,
        were completely cut off. So the people crossed [the river] opposite Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And while all [the people of] Israel crossed over on dry ground, the
        priests who carried the ark of the covenant of the Lord stood firm on dry
        ground in the midst of the Jordan [riverbed], until all the nation had finished
        crossing over the Jordan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Memorial Stones from Jordan'
      title: Memorial Stones from Jordan
      number: 1
      content: '  So it was when all the nation had finished crossing the Jordan,
        the Lord said to Joshua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTake for yourselves the twelve men [chosen] from among the
        people, one man from each tribe, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and command them, \u2018Pick up for yourselves twelve stones [one
        each] from here out of the midst of the Jordan, from the place where the
        priests\u2019 feet are standing firm; carry them over with you and lay them
        down at the place where you will spend the night tonight.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Joshua called the twelve men whom he had appointed from the
        sons of Israel, one man from each tribe; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and Joshua said to them, \u201CCross over again to the ark of the
        Lord your God into the midst of the Jordan, and each of you take up a stone
        on his shoulder, according to the number of the tribes of the sons of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "so that this may be a sign among you; when your children ask later,
        \u2018What do these stones mean to you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "then you shall say to them that the waters of the Jordan were cut
        off before the ark of the covenant of the Lord; when it crossed the Jordan,
        the waters of the Jordan were cut off. So these stones shall become a memorial
        for Israel forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the [twelve men chosen from the] sons of Israel did as Joshua
        commanded, and took up twelve stones out of the midst of the Jordan, according
        to the number of the tribes of the sons of Israel, just as the Lord had spoken
        to Joshua; and they carried them over with them to the place where they were
        spending the night and put them down there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Joshua set up [a second monument of] twelve stones in the midst
        of the Jordan at the place where the feet of the priests who carried the
        ark of the covenant were standing, and they are there to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the priests who carried the ark were standing in the midst of
        the Jordan until everything was finished that the Lord had commanded Joshua
        to tell the people, in accordance with everything that Moses had commanded
        Joshua. The people hurried and crossed [the dry riverbed]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and when all the people had finished crossing, the ark of the Lord
        and the priests crossed over in the presence of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad and half the tribe of Manasseh
        crossed over armed for battle before the [other] sons of Israel, just as
        Moses had spoken to them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'about 40,000 [men] armed and equipped for war crossed for battle
        before the Lord to the desert plains of Jericho.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'On that day the Lord magnified and exalted Joshua in the sight of
        all Israel; so they feared him [with profound awe and reverence], just as
        they had feared Moses all the days of his life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now the Lord said to Joshua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201COrder the priests carrying the ark of the Testimony to come
        up out of the Jordan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Joshua commanded the priests, saying, \u201CCome up out of the
        Jordan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When the priests who carried the ark of the covenant of the Lord
        had come up from the midst of the Jordan, and the soles of their feet were
        raised up to the dry land, the waters of the Jordan returned to their place,
        and flowed over all its banks as before.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the people came up from the Jordan on the tenth [day] of the
        first month and encamped at Gilgal on the eastern border of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And those twelve stones which they had taken from the Jordan, Joshua
        set up in Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "He said to the sons of Israel, \u201CWhen your children ask their
        fathers in time to come, \u2018What do these stones mean?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "then you shall let your children know, \u2018Israel crossed this
        Jordan on dry ground.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the Lord your God dried up the waters of the Jordan for you until
        you crossed over, just as the Lord your God did to the Red Sea, which He
        dried up before us until we had crossed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "so that all the peoples of the earth may know [without any doubt]
        and acknowledge that the hand of the Lord is mighty and extraordinarily powerful,
        so that you will fear the Lord your God [and obey and worship Him with profound
        awe and reverence] forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Is Circumcised'
      title: Israel Is Circumcised
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it happened when all the kings of the Amorites who were beyond
        the Jordan to the west, and all the kings of the Canaanites who were by the
        sea, heard that the Lord had dried up the waters of the Jordan before the
        Israelites until they had crossed over, their hearts melted [in despair],
        and there was no [fighting] spirit in them any longer because of the Israelites
        [and what God had done for them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "At that time the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CMake for yourself flint
        knives and circumcise the [new generation of the] sons of Israel as [was
        done] before.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Joshua made flint knives and circumcised the sons of Israel at
        Gibeath-haaraloth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This is the reason why Joshua circumcised them: all the people who
        came out of Egypt who were males, all the men of war, had died in the wilderness
        along the way after they left Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All the males who came out were circumcised, but all the males who
        were born in the wilderness on the way as they left Egypt had not been circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the Israelites walked forty years in the wilderness, until all
        the nation, that is, the men of war who came out of Egypt, died because they
        did not listen to the voice of the Lord; to them the Lord had sworn [an oath]
        that He would not let them see the land which He had promised to their fathers
        to give us, a land [of abundance] flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So it was their uncircumcised sons whom He raised up in their place,
        whom Joshua circumcised, because circumcision had not been performed on the
        way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then, when they had finished circumcising all [the males of] the
        nation, they stayed in their places in the camp until they were healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CThis day I have rolled away the
        reproach (derision, ridicule) of Egypt from you.\u201D So the name of that
        place is called Gilgal (rolling) to this day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'While the Israelites camped at Gilgal they observed the Passover
        on the evening of the fourteenth day of the month on the desert plains of
        Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'On the day after Passover, on that very day, they ate some of the
        produce of the land, unleavened bread, and roasted grain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the manna ceased on the day after they had eaten some of the
        produce of the land, so that the Israelites no longer had manna, but they
        ate some of the produce of the land of Canaan during that year.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now when Joshua was by Jericho, he looked up, and behold, a man was
        standing opposite him with his drawn sword in his hand, and Joshua went to
        him and said to him, \u201CAre you for us or for our adversaries?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He said, \u201CNo; rather I have come now as captain of the army
        of the Lord.\u201D Then Joshua fell with his face toward the earth and bowed
        down, and said to him, \u201CWhat does my lord have to say to his servant?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The captain of the Lord\u2019s army said to Joshua, \u201CRemove
        your sandals from your feet, because the place where you are standing is
        holy (set apart to the Lord).\u201D And Joshua did so."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Conquest of Jericho'
      title: The Conquest of Jericho
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Jericho [a fortified city with high walls] was tightly closed
        because [of the people\u2019s fear] of the sons of Israel; no one went out
        or came in. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "The Lord said to Joshua, \u201CSee, I have given Jericho into your
        hand, with its king and the mighty warriors. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now you shall march around the city, all the men of war circling
        the city once. You shall do this [once each day] for six days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Also, seven priests shall carry seven trumpets [made] of rams\u2019
        horns ahead of the ark; then on the seventh day you shall march around the
        city seven times, and the priests shall blow the trumpets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "When they make a long blast with the ram\u2019s horn, and when you
        hear the sound of the trumpet, all the people shall cry out with a great
        shout (battle cry); and the wall of the city will fall down in its place,
        and the people shall go up, each man [going] straight ahead [climbing over
        the rubble].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Joshua the son of Nun called for the priests and said to them,
        \u201CTake up the ark of the covenant, and have seven priests carry seven
        trumpets made of rams\u2019 horns ahead of the ark of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He said to the people, \u201CGo forward! March around the city, and
        let the armed men go ahead of the ark of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And it was so, that when Joshua had spoken to the people, the seven
        priests carrying the seven trumpets made of rams\u2019 horns went on before
        the Lord and blew the trumpets; then the ark of the covenant of the Lord
        went behind them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The armed men went in front of the priests who blew the trumpets,
        and the rear guard came after the ark, while the priests continued to blow
        the trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Joshua commanded the people, \u201CYou shall not shout [the battle
        cry] nor let your voice be heard nor let a word come out of your mouth, until
        the day I tell you to shout. Then you shall shout!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So Joshua had the ark of the Lord taken around the city [on the first
        day], circling it once; then they came back into the camp and spent the night
        in the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Joshua got up early in the morning [on the second day], and
        the priests took up the ark of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The seven priests carrying the seven trumpets made of rams\u2019
        horns ahead of the ark of the Lord went on continually, blowing the trumpets;
        and the armed men went ahead of them and the rear guard came after the ark
        of the Lord, while the priests continued to blow the trumpets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'On the second day they marched around the city once, and returned
        to the camp; they did this for six days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then on the seventh day they got up early at daybreak and marched
        around the city in the same way seven times; only on that day they marched
        around the city seven times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And the seventh time, when the priests had blown the trumpets, Joshua
        said to the people, \u201CShout! For the Lord has given you the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The city and everything that is in it shall be under the ban [that
        is, designated to be destroyed as a form of tribute] to the Lord; only Rahab
        the prostitute and all [the people] who are with her in her house shall [be
        allowed to] live, because she hid and protected the messengers (scouts) whom
        we sent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But as for you, keep yourselves [away] from the things under the
        ban [which are to be destroyed], so that you do not covet them and take some
        of the things under the ban [for personal gain], and put the camp of Israel
        under the ban (doomed to destruction), and bring disaster upon it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "All the silver and gold and articles of bronze and iron are holy
        (consecrated) to the Lord; they shall go into the treasury of the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So the people shouted [the battle cry], and the priests blew the
        trumpets. When the people heard the sound of the trumpet, they raised a great
        shout and the wall [of Jericho] fell down, so that the sons of Israel went
        up into the city, every man straight ahead [climbing over the rubble], and
        they overthrew the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they utterly destroyed everything that was in the city, both
        man and woman, young and old, and ox and sheep and donkey, with the edge
        of the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Joshua said to the two men who had spied out the land, \u201CGo
        into the prostitute\u2019s house and bring the woman and all that she has
        out of there, as you have sworn to her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the young men, the spies, went in and brought out Rahab and her
        father and her mother and her brothers and everything that she had; they
        also brought out all her relatives and allowed them to stay outside the camp
        of Israel [at Gilgal during the time required for ceremonial cleansing]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then they completely burned the city and everything that was in it.
        They put only the silver and the gold, and the articles of bronze and of
        iron, into the treasury of the house (tabernacle) of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So Joshua spared Rahab the prostitute, with her father\u2019s household
        and everything that she had; and she has lived among Israel to this day,
        because she hid the messengers (scouts) whom Joshua sent to spy out Jericho.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then Joshua made them take an oath at that time, saying, \u201CCursed
        before the Lord is the man who rises up and rebuilds this city, Jericho;
        with the loss of his firstborn he shall lay its foundation, and with the
        loss of his youngest son he shall set up its gates.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: So the Lord was with Joshua, and his fame was in all the land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Is Defeated at Ai'
      title: Israel Is Defeated at Ai
      number: 1
      content: '  But the sons of Israel acted unfaithfully and violated their obligation
        in regard to the things [off limits] under the ban [those things belonging
        to the Lord], for Achan, the son of Carmi, the son of Zabdi, the son of Zerah,
        from the tribe of Judah, took some of the things under the ban [for personal
        gain]. Therefore the anger of the Lord burned against the Israelites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai, which is near Beth-aven,
        east of Bethel, and said to them, \u201CGo up and spy out the land.\u201D
        So the men went up and spied out Ai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then they returned to Joshua and said to him, \u201CDo not make all
        the people go up [to fight]; have only about two thousand or three thousand
        men go up and attack Ai; do not make the entire army go up there, for they
        [of Ai] are few.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So about three thousand men from the sons of Israel went up there,
        but they fled [in retreat] from the men of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The men of Ai killed about thirty-six of Israel\u2019s men, and chased
        them from the gate as far as [the bluffs of] Shebarim and struck them down
        as they descended [the steep pass], so the hearts of the people melted [in
        despair and began to doubt God\u2019s promise] and became like water (disheartened).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Joshua tore his clothes and fell face downward on the ground
        before the ark of the Lord until evening, he and the elders of Israel; and
        [with great sorrow] they put dust on their heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Joshua said, \u201CAlas, O Lord God, why have You brought this people
        across the Jordan at all, only to hand us over to the Amorites, to destroy
        us? If only we had been willing to live beyond the Jordan! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Lord, what can I say now that [the army of] Israel has turned back
        [in retreat and fled] before their enemies? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For the Canaanites and all the inhabitants of the land will hear
        about it, and will surround us and cut off our name from the earth. And what
        will You do for Your great name [to keep it from dishonor]?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CGet up! Why is it that you have
        fallen on your face? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Israel has sinned; they have also transgressed My covenant which
        I commanded them [to keep]. They have even taken some of the things under
        the ban, and they have both stolen and denied [the theft]. Moreover, they
        have also put the stolen objects among their own things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'That is why the soldiers of Israel could not stand [and defend themselves]
        before their enemies; they turned their backs [and ran] before them, because
        they have become accursed. I will not be with you anymore unless you destroy
        the things under the ban from among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Rise up! Consecrate the people and say, \u2018Consecrate yourselves
        for tomorrow, for thus says the Lord, the God of Israel: \u201CThere are
        things under the ban among you, O Israel. You cannot stand [victorious] before
        your enemies until you remove the things under the ban from among you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the morning you shall come forward by your tribes. And it shall
        be that the tribe which the Lord chooses by lot shall come forward by families,
        and the family which the Lord chooses shall come forward by [separate] households,
        and the household which the Lord chooses shall come forward man by man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Sin of Achan'
      title: The Sin of Achan
      number: 15
      content: "It shall be that the one who is chosen with the things under the
        ban shall be [killed and his body] burned with fire, he and all that belongs
        to him, because he has transgressed the covenant of the Lord, and because
        he has done a disgraceful and disobedient thing in Israel.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Joshua got up early in the morning and had Israel come forward
        by tribes, and the tribe of Judah was chosen [by lot]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He had the families of Judah come forward, and the family of the
        Zerahites was chosen; and he had the family of the Zerahites come forward
        man by man, and Zabdi was chosen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He brought his household forward man by man; and Achan the son of
        Carmi, son of Zabdi, son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, was chosen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Joshua said to Achan, \u201CMy son, I implore you, give glory
        to the Lord, the God of Israel, and give praise to Him [in recognition of
        His righteous judgments]; and tell me now what you have done. Do not hide
        it from me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So Achan answered Joshua and said, \u201CIn truth, I have sinned
        against the Lord, the God of Israel, and this is what I have done: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "when I saw among the spoils [in Jericho] a beautiful robe from Shinar
        (southern Babylon) and two hundred shekels of silver and a bar of gold weighing
        fifty shekels, I wanted them and took them. Behold, they are hidden in the
        ground inside my tent, with the silver underneath.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Joshua sent messengers, and they ran to the tent; and they saw
        the stolen objects hidden in his tent, with the silver underneath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they took them from the tent and brought them to Joshua and to
        all the sons of Israel, and spread them out before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him, took Achan the son of Zerah,
        the silver, the [royal] robe, the bar of gold, his sons, his daughters, his
        oxen, his donkeys, his sheep, his tent, and everything that he had; and they
        brought them up to the Valley of Achor (Disaster). '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Joshua said, \u201CWhy have you brought disaster on us? The Lord
        will bring you disaster this day.\u201D Then all Israel stoned them [to death]
        with stones; afterward they burned their bodies in the fire. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: Then they piled up over him a great heap of stones that remains to
        this day. Then the Lord turned from the fierceness of His anger. Therefore
        the name of that place has been called the Valley of Achor (Disaster) to
        this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Conquest of Ai'
      title: The Conquest of Ai
      number: 1
      content: "  Now the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CDo not fear or be dismayed (intimidated).
        Take all the men of war with you and set out, go up to Ai; see, I have given
        the king of Ai, his people, his city, and his land into your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "You shall do [the same] to Ai and its king as you did to Jericho
        and its king; [except that] you shall take only its spoil and its cattle
        as plunder for yourselves. Set up an ambush for the city behind it [on the
        west side].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Joshua set out with all the people of war to go up against Ai;
        then Joshua chose thirty thousand valiant men, and sent them out at night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He commanded them, saying, \u201CListen closely, you are going to
        lie in wait and ambush the city from behind it. Do not go very far away from
        the city, but all of you be ready. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then I and all the people who are with me will approach the city.
        And when they come out to meet us [for battle] as [they did] the first time,
        we will run away from them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They will come out after us until we have lured them away from the
        city, because they will say, \u2018They are running from us as [they did]
        before.\u2019 So we will run from them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then you will emerge from the ambush and take possession of the city,
        for the Lord your God will hand it over to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When you have taken the city, you shall set it on fire; you shall
        do [exactly] as the Lord commanded. See, I have commanded you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Joshua sent them off, and they went to the place for the ambush
        and stayed [hidden] between Bethel and Ai, on the west side of Ai; but Joshua
        spent that night among the people [in Gilgal].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now Joshua got up early in the morning and assembled the people,
        and went up with the elders of Israel before the people to Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then all the fighting men who were with him went up and advanced
        and arrived in front of the city, and camped on the north side of Ai. Now
        there was a ravine between them and Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And Joshua took about five thousand men and set them in ambush between
        Bethel and Ai, on the west side of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So they stationed the people, all the army\u2014the main encampment
        that was north of the city, and their rear guard on the west side of the
        city\u2014and Joshua spent that night in the valley. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now when the king [and the people] of Ai saw it, the men of the city
        hurried and got up early and went out to meet Israel in battle, the king
        and all his people at the appointed [time and] place before the desert plain
        (the Arabah). But he did not know that there was an ambush against him [waiting]
        behind the city [on the west side]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Joshua and all Israel pretended to be defeated by them, and ran
        toward the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then all the people who were in the city were called together to
        pursue them, and they pursued Joshua and were lured away from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Not a man was left in Ai or Bethel who had not gone out after Israel;
        so they left the city open and unguarded and they pursued Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CReach out with the spear that
        is in your hand [and point it] toward Ai, for I will give it into your hand.\u201D
        So Joshua reached out with the spear in his hand [and pointed it] toward
        the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The [men in] ambush emerged quickly from their [hiding] place, and
        when Joshua stretched out his hand they ran and entered the city and captured
        it, and quickly set the city on fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When the men of Ai turned back and looked, behold, the smoke of the
        city was ascending toward the sky, and they had no opportunity to run this
        way or that way. Then the people who had been running to the wilderness turned
        back toward the pursuers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Joshua and all Israel saw that the [men in] ambush had taken
        the city and that the smoke of the city was ascending, they turned back and
        struck down the men of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the others came out of the city to confront the men of Ai [as
        they returned], so that they were trapped in the midst of Israel, some on
        this side and some on that side; then Israel struck them until none of them
        survived or escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But they took the king of Ai alive and brought him to Joshua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Israel had finished killing all the inhabitants of Ai in the
        field in the wilderness where they pursued them, and they had all fallen
        by the edge of the sword until they were destroyed, then all Israel returned
        to Ai and struck it with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And all who fell that day, both men and women, were twelve thousand,
        all the people of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For Joshua did not withdraw his hand with which he stretched out
        the spear until he had utterly destroyed all the inhabitants of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Israel took only the livestock and the spoil of that city as plunder
        for themselves, according to the word of the Lord which He had commanded
        Joshua. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Joshua burned Ai and made it a rubbish heap forever, a desolation
        until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He hanged [the body of] the king of Ai on a tree [leaving it there]
        until evening; at sunset Joshua gave a command and they took the body down
        from the tree and dumped it at the entrance of the city gate, and piled a
        great heap of stones over it that stands to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Joshua built an altar to the Lord, the God of Israel, on Mount
        Ebal, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'just as Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded the sons of Israel,
        as it is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, an altar of uncut stones
        on which no one has wielded an iron tool; and they offered on it burnt offerings
        to the Lord, and sacrificed peace offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And there, in the presence of the sons of Israel, Joshua wrote on
        the stones a copy of the Law of Moses which Moses had written. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'All Israel, the stranger as well as the native born [among them],
        with their elders and officers and their judges, stood on either side of
        the ark before the Levitical priests who carried the ark of the covenant
        of the Lord. Half of them stood in front of Mount Gerizim and half of them
        in front of Mount Ebal, just as Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded
        at first to bless the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then afterward Joshua read all the words of the law, the blessing
        and curse, according to all that is written in the Book of the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: There was not a word of all that Moses had commanded which Joshua
        did not read before the entire assembly of Israel, including the women and
        the children and the foreigners who were living among them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Guile of the Gibeonites'
      title: Guile of the Gibeonites
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when all the kings who were beyond the Jordan, in the hill
        country and in the lowland [at the western edge of the hills of Judea], and
        all along the coast of the Great [Mediterranean] Sea toward Lebanon, the
        Hittite and the Amorite, the Canaanite, the Perizzite, the Hivite and the
        Jebusite, heard of this [army and its victories over Jericho and Ai], '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'they gathered together with one purpose to fight with Joshua and
        with Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But when the people of Gibeon [the Hivites] heard what Joshua had
        done to Jericho and Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'they too acted craftily and cunningly, and set out and took along
        provisions, but took worn-out sacks on their donkeys, and wineskins (leather
        bottles) that were worn out and split open and patched together, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and worn-out and patched sandals on their feet, and worn-out clothes;
        and all their supply of food was dry and had turned to crumbs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They went to Joshua in the camp at Gilgal and said to him and the
        men of Israel, \u201CWe have come from a far country; so now, make a covenant
        (treaty) with us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the men of Israel said to the Hivites, \u201CPerhaps you are
        living within our land; how then can we make a covenant (treaty) with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They said to Joshua, \u201CWe are your servants.\u201D Then Joshua
        said to them, \u201CWho are you, and where do you come from?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They said to him, \u201CYour servants have come from a country that
        is very far away because of the fame of the Lord your God; for we have heard
        the news about Him and all [the remarkable things] that He did in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and everything that He did to the two kings of the Amorites who were
        beyond the Jordan, to Sihon the king of Heshbon and to Og the king of Bashan
        who lived in Ashtaroth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So our elders and all the residents of our country said to us, \u2018Take
        provisions for the journey and go to meet the sons of Israel and say to them,
        \u201CWe are your servants; now make a covenant (treaty) with us.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'This bread of ours was hot (fresh) when we took it along as our provision
        from our houses on the day we left to come to you; now look, it is dry and
        has turned to crumbs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "These wineskins which we filled were new, and look, they are split;
        our clothes and our sandals are worn out because of the very long journey
        [that we had to make].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the men [of Israel] took some of their own provisions [and offered
        them in friendship], and [foolishly] did not ask for the counsel of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Joshua made peace with them and made a covenant (treaty) with them,
        to let them live; and the leaders of the congregation [of Israel] swore an
        oath to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'It happened that three days after they had made a covenant (treaty)
        with them, the Israelites heard that they were [actually] their neighbors
        and that they were living among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the sons of Israel set out and came to their cities on the third
        day. Now the cities [of the Hivites] were Gibeon and Chephirah and Beeroth
        and Kiriath-jearim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the sons of Israel did not strike them because the leaders of
        the congregation had sworn to them by the Lord the God of Israel [to spare
        them]. And all the congregation murmured [expressing great dissatisfaction]
        against the leaders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But all the leaders said to the whole congregation, \u201CWe have
        sworn to them by the Lord, the God of Israel, so now we cannot touch them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "This [is what] we will do to them: we will let them live, so that
        the wrath [of God] does not come upon us for [violating] the oath which we
        have sworn to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The leaders said to them, \u201CLet them live [as our slaves].\u201D
        So they became the cutters and gatherers of firewood and water carriers for
        the entire congregation, just as the leaders had said of them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Joshua called the [Hivite] men and said, \u201CWhy did you deceive
        us, saying, \u2018We live very far away from you,\u2019 when [in fact] you
        live among us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now therefore, you are cursed, and you shall always be slaves, both
        cutters and gatherers of firewood and water carriers for the house of my
        God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They replied to Joshua and said, \u201CBecause your servants were
        told in no uncertain terms that the Lord your God commanded His servant Moses
        to give you all the land, and to destroy all the land\u2019s inhabitants
        before you, we feared greatly for our lives because of you, and so we did
        this [deceptive] thing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now look, we are in your hands; do to us as it seems good and right
        in your sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So that is what he did to them; he rescued them from the hands of
        the Israelites and they did not kill them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Now on that day Joshua made them cutters and gatherers of firewood
        and water carriers for the congregation and for the altar of the Lord, to
        this day, in the place which He would choose.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Five Kings Attack Gibeon'
      title: Five Kings Attack Gibeon
      number: 1
      content: "  When Adoni-zedek king of Jerusalem heard that Joshua had captured
        Ai, and had utterly destroyed it\u2014as he had done to Jericho and its king,
        so he had done to Ai and its king\u2014and that the residents of Gibeon had
        made peace with Israel and were [living] among them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'he [and his people] feared greatly, because Gibeon was a great city,
        like one of the royal cities, and because it was greater than Ai, and all
        its men were mighty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Adoni-zedek king of Jerusalem sent word to Hoham king of Hebron,
        and to Piram king of Jarmuth, to Japhia king of Lachish, and to Debir king
        of Eglon, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CCome up to me and help me, and let us attack Gibeon [with a
        combined army], because it has made peace with Joshua and with the sons (people)
        of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the five kings of the Amorites, the king of Jerusalem, the king
        of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon,
        gathered together and went up, they with all their armies, and they camped
        by Gibeon and fought against it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the men of Gibeon sent word to Joshua at the camp in Gilgal, saying,
        \u201CDo not abandon your servants; come up to us quickly and save us and
        help us, for all [five of] the kings of the Amorites who live in the hill
        country have assembled against us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joshua went up from Gilgal, he and all the people of war with
        him, and all the men of valor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord said to Joshua, \u201CDo not fear them, because I have given
        them into your hand; not one of them shall stand before you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Joshua came upon them suddenly, [surprising them] by marching
        [uphill] all night from Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the Lord caused them to panic and be confused before Israel,
        and He struck them dead in a great slaughter at Gibeon, and chased them along
        the way that goes up to Beth-horon and struck them as far as Azekah and Makkedah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As they fled before Israel, while they were at the descent of Beth-horon,
        the Lord threw down large stones [of hail] from heaven on them as far as
        Azekah, and they died. More [Amorites] died because of the hailstones than
        those whom the sons of Israel killed with the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Joshua spoke to the Lord on the day when the Lord handed over
        the Amorites to the sons of Israel, and Joshua said in the sight of Israel,\u201CSun,
        stand still at Gibeon,And moon, in the Valley of Aijalon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the sun stood still, and the moon stopped,Until the nation [of
        Israel] took vengeance upon their enemies.Is it not written in the Book of
        Jashar? So the sun stood still in the middle of the sky and was in no hurry
        to go down for about a whole day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There has not been a day like that before it or after it, when the
        Lord listened to (heeded) the voice of a man; for the Lord was fighting for
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Victory at Makkedah'
      title: Victory at Makkedah
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him returned to the camp at Gilgal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now these five [Amorite] kings fled and hid themselves in the cave
        at Makkedah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Joshua was told, \u201CThe five kings have been found and are
        hidden in the cave at Makkedah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Joshua said, \u201CRoll large stones against the mouth of the cave,
        and assign men by it to guard them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "but do not stay there yourselves; pursue your enemies and attack
        them from the rear. Do not allow them to enter their cities, for the Lord
        your God has given them into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now when Joshua and the sons of Israel had finished striking the
        Amorites dead in a very great defeat, until they were wiped out, and the
        surviving remnant among them had entered the fortified cities, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'all the people returned to the camp to Joshua at Makkedah in peace.
        No one uttered a [threatening] word against any of the sons of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Joshua said, \u201COpen the mouth of the cave and bring out
        to me those five [Amorite] kings from the cave.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "They did so, and brought these five [Amorite] kings out of the cave
        to him\u2014the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth,
        the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "When they brought these kings out to Joshua, Joshua called for all
        the men of Israel, and told the commanders of the men of war who had gone
        with him, \u201CCome up close, put your feet on the necks of these kings.\u201D
        So they came forward and put their feet on the necks [of the five kings]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Joshua said to them, \u201CDo not fear or be dismayed (intimidated)!
        Be strong and courageous, for this is what the Lord will do to all your enemies
        against whom you [are about to] fight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Then afterward Joshua struck them [with his sword] and put them to
        death, and he hung them on five trees; and they hung on the trees until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'At sunset Joshua gave a command, and they took the bodies down from
        the trees and threw them into the cave where the kings had hidden themselves,
        and placed large stones over the mouth of the cave, [where they remain] to
        this very day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Joshua\u2019s Conquest of Southern Canaan"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Conquest of Southern Canaan"
      number: 28
      content: 'Now Joshua captured Makkedah on that day, and struck it and its king
        with the edge of the sword; he utterly destroyed it and everyone who was
        in it. He left no survivor. So he did to the king of Makkedah just as he
        had done to the king of Jericho.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him went on from Makkedah to Libnah,
        and fought against Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The Lord gave it also along with its king into the hands of Israel,
        and Joshua struck it and every person who was in it with the edge of the
        sword. He left no survivor in it. So he did to the king of Libnah just as
        he had done to the king of Jericho.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And Joshua and all Israel with him moved on from Libnah to Lachish,
        and they camped by it and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The Lord gave Lachish into the hands of Israel; and Joshua captured
        it on the second day, and struck it and every person who was in it with the
        edge of the sword, just as he had done to Libnah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Horam king of Gezer went up to help Lachish, and Joshua struck
        him and his people down until he had left him no survivor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And Joshua and all Israel with him went on from Lachish to Eglon,
        and they camped by it and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'They captured it on that day and struck it with the edge of the sword;
        and on that day he utterly destroyed every person who was in it, just as
        he had done to Lachish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him went up from Eglon to Hebron,
        and they fought against it '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and captured it and struck it and its king and all its cities and
        all the persons who were in it with the edge of the sword. He left no survivor,
        just as he had done to Eglon. He utterly destroyed it and every person who
        was in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him returned to Debir, and fought
        against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'He captured it with its king and all its cities, and they struck
        them with the edge of the sword, and utterly destroyed every person who was
        in it. He left no survivor. Just as he had done to Hebron, so Joshua did
        to Debir and its king, as he had done also to Libnah and its king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So Joshua struck all the land, the hill country, the Negev (South
        country) and the lowland and the slopes [that descend to the Dead Sea] and
        all their kings. He left no survivor, but he utterly destroyed all who breathed,
        just as the Lord, the God of Israel, had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Joshua struck them from Kadesh-barnea even as far as Gaza, and all
        the country of Goshen even as far as Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Joshua captured all these kings and their land at one time, because
        the Lord, the God of Israel, fought for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: So Joshua and all Israel with him returned to the camp at Gilgal.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Northern Canaan Taken'
      title: Northern Canaan Taken
      number: 1
      content: "  Then when Jabin king of Hazor heard [of Israel\u2019s other victories]
        he sent word to Jobab king of Madon, and to the king of Shimron, and to the
        king of Achshaph, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and to the kings who were in the north, in the hill country, and
        in the Arabah [the plain] south of Chinnereth (the Sea of Galilee) and in
        the lowland and on the hills of Dor on the west; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'to the Canaanite in the east and in the west, and to the Amorite,
        the Hittite, the Perizzite, and the Jebusite in the hill country, and the
        Hivite at the foot of [Mount] Hermon in the land of Mizpeh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They went out, they and all their armies with them, as many people
        as the sand on the seashore, with very many horses and chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So all these kings met and they came and encamped together at the
        waters of Merom, to fight against Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the Lord said to Joshua, \u201CDo not be afraid because of them,
        for tomorrow by this time I am going to hand over all of them slain [by the
        sword] to Israel; you shall hamstring (disable) their horses and set fire
        to their chariots.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joshua and all the people of war with him came against them suddenly
        by the waters of Merom, and attacked them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord handed them over to Israel, who struck them and pursued
        them as far as Great Sidon and Misrephoth-maim and eastward as far as the
        Valley of Mizpeh; they struck them down until no survivor was left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Joshua did to them as the Lord had told him; he hamstrung (disabled)
        their horses and set fire to their chariots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'At that time Joshua turned back and captured Hazor and struck its
        king dead with the sword; for Hazor previously was the head of all these
        kingdoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They struck all the people who were in it with the edge of the sword,
        utterly destroying them; there was no one left who breathed. And he set fire
        to Hazor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Joshua captured all the cities of these kings, and all their kings,
        and he struck them with the edge of the sword, utterly destroying them, just
        as Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But Israel did not burn any of the cities that stood [walled and
        fortified] on their mounds, except Hazor alone, which Joshua burned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The sons of Israel took as their plunder all the spoil of these cities
        and the cattle; but they struck every man with the edge of the sword, until
        they had destroyed them. They left no one alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Just as the Lord had commanded Moses His servant, so Moses had commanded
        Joshua, and so Joshua did; he left nothing undone of all that the Lord had
        commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Joshua took all this land: the hill country, all the Negev (South
        country), all the land of Goshen, the lowland, the Arabah [plain], the hill
        country of Israel and its lowland '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'from Mount Halak, that rises toward Seir [in the south], even as
        far as Baal-gad in the Valley of Lebanon at the foot of Mount Hermon [in
        the north]. He captured all their kings and struck them and put them to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Joshua waged war with all these kings a long time [at least five
        years]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'There was no city that made peace with the Israelites except the
        Hivites living in Gibeon; they took all the others in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For it was [the purpose] of the Lord to harden their hearts, to meet
        Israel in battle so that Israel would utterly destroy them, that they would
        receive no mercy, but that Israel would destroy them, just as the Lord had
        commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then Joshua came at that time and cut off the Anakim from the hill
        country, from Hebron, from Debir, from Anab and from all the hill country
        of Judah and all the hill country of Israel. Joshua utterly destroyed them
        with their cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'There were no Anakim left in the land of the children of Israel;
        only in Gaza, in Gath, and in Ashdod [of Philistia] some remained. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So Joshua took the whole land [of Canaan], according to all that the
        Lord had spoken to Moses, and Joshua gave it as an inheritance to Israel
        according to their divisions by their tribes. So the land had rest from war.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Kings Defeated by Israel'
      title: Kings Defeated by Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the kings of the land whom the sons of Israel defeated,
        and whose land they possessed beyond the Jordan toward the east, from the
        valley of the [river] Arnon to Mount Hermon, and all the Arabah [plain] to
        the east: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sihon king of the Amorites, who lived in Heshbon, and ruled from
        Aroer, which is on the edge of the valley of the [river] Arnon, both the
        middle of the valley and half of Gilead, and as far as the brook Jabbok,
        [which is] the border of the sons of Ammon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the Arabah [plain] as far as the Sea of Chinnereth (Galilee)
        eastward, and as far as the sea of the Arabah, the Salt (Dead) Sea, eastward
        toward Beth-jeshimoth, and southward to the foot of the slopes of [Mount]
        Pisgah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and the territory of Og king of Bashan, one of the remnant of the
        Rephaim, who lived at Ashtaroth and at Edrei, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and ruled over Mount Hermon and Salecah and all of Bashan to the
        border of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and over half of Gilead, as
        far as the border of Sihon king of Heshbon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Moses the servant of the Lord and the sons of Israel defeated them;
        and Moses the servant of the Lord gave their land as a possession to the
        Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'These are the kings of the land whom Joshua and the sons of Israel
        defeated on the west side of the Jordan, from Baal-gad in the Valley of Lebanon
        to Mount Halak, which rises toward Seir. Joshua gave their land to the tribes
        of Israel as a possession according to their divisions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "in the hill country, in the lowland (foothills), in the Arabah [plain],
        on the slopes [descending to the Dead Sea], and in the wilderness, and in
        the Negev (South country)\u2014the [lands of the] Hittite, the Amorite and
        the Canaanite, the Perizzite, the Hivite and the Jebusite: "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the king of Jericho, one; the king of Ai, which is beside Bethel,
        one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the king of Jerusalem, one; the king of Hebron, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the king of Jarmuth, one; the king of Lachish, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the king of Eglon, one; the king of Gezer, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the king of Debir, one; the king of Geder, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the king of Hormah, one; the king of Arad, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the king of Libnah, one; the king of Adullam, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the king of Makkedah, one; the king of Bethel, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the king of Tappuah, one; the king of Hepher, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the king of Aphek, one; the king of Lasharon, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the king of Madon, one; the king of Hazor, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the king of Shimron-meron, one; the king of Achshaph, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the king of Taanach, one; the king of Megiddo, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'the king of Kedesh, one; the king of Jokneam in Carmel, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the king of Dor in the heights of Dor, one; the king of Goiim in
        Gilgal, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the king of Tirzah, one: in all, thirty-one kings.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Canaan Divided among the Tribes'
      title: Canaan Divided among the Tribes
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Joshua was old and advanced in years, and the Lord said to
        him, \u201CYou have grown old and advanced in years, and very substantial
        portions of the land remain to be possessed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This is the land that remains: all the regions of the Philistines
        and all those of the Geshurites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'from the Shihor [waterway] which is east of Egypt [at the southern
        end of Canaan], northward to the border of Ekron (all of it regarded as Canaanite);
        the five rulers of the Philistines: the Gazite, Ashdodite, the Ashkelonite,
        the Gittite, the Ekronite; and the Avvite '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'in the south, all the land of the Canaanite, and Mearah that belongs
        to the Sidonians, as far as Aphek, to the border of the Amorite; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and the land of the Gebalite, and all Lebanon, toward the east, from
        Baal-gad below Mount Hermon to the entrance of Hamath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'As for all the inhabitants of the hill country from Lebanon to Misrephoth-maim,
        even all the Sidonians, I will drive them out before Israel; only allot the
        land to Israel as an inheritance just as I have commanded you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So now, divide this land [west of the Jordan] as an inheritance for
        the nine tribes and the half-tribe of Manasseh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'With the other half-tribe [of Manasseh], the Reubenites and the Gadites
        received their inheritance which Moses gave them beyond the Jordan eastward,
        just as Moses the servant of the Lord gave to them; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'from Aroer on the edge of the valley of the [river] Arnon, and the
        city in the middle of the valley, and all the plain of Medeba, as far as
        Dibon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in
        Heshbon, as far as the border of the Ammonites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and Gilead, and the territory of the Geshurites and Maacathites,
        and all Mount Hermon, and all Bashan as far as Salecah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "the entire kingdom of Og in Bashan, who reigned in Ashtaroth and
        Edrei\u2014he alone was left of the remnant of the Rephaim [giants]\u2014for
        Moses had struck them and dispossessed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But the sons of Israel did not dispossess the Geshurites or the Maacathites;
        for Geshur and Maacath live among Israel to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'It was only to the tribe of Levi that Moses gave no [territory as
        an] inheritance; the offerings by fire to the Lord, the God of Israel, are
        their inheritance, as He told him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Moses gave an inheritance to the tribe of the sons of Reuben according
        to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Their territory was from Aroer, which is on the edge of the valley
        of the [river] Arnon, and the city which is in the middle of the valley and
        all the plain by Medeba; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'with Heshbon, and all its cities which are on the plain: Dibon and
        Bamoth-baal and Beth-baal-meon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and Jahaz and Kedemoth and Mephaath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and Kiriathaim and Sibmah and Zereth-shahar on the hill of the valley, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and Beth-peor and the slopes of Pisgah and Beth-jeshimoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'even all the cities of the plain and all the kingdom of Sihon king
        of the Amorites who reigned in Heshbon, whom Moses struck down along with
        the leaders of Midian, Evi and Rekem and Zur and Hur and Reba, the princes
        of Sihon, who lived in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Israel also killed Balaam the son of Beor, the diviner
        (soothsayer), with the sword among [the rest of] their slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The border of the sons of Reuben was the Jordan. This was the inheritance
        of the sons of Reuben according to their families, with their cities and
        villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Moses also gave an inheritance to the tribe of Gad, to the sons of
        Gad, according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their territory was Jazer, and all the cities of Gilead, and half
        the land of the sons of Ammon, as far as Aroer east of Rabbah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and from Heshbon as far as Ramath-mizpeh and Betonim, and from Mahanaim
        as far as the border of Debir; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and in the valley, Beth-haram and Beth-nimrah and Succoth and Zaphon,
        the rest of the kingdom of Sihon king of Heshbon, with the Jordan as a border,
        as far as the lower end of the Sea of Chinnereth (Galilee) east of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the sons of Gad according to their families,
        with their cities and their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Moses also gave an inheritance to the half-tribe of Manasseh; and
        it was for the half-tribe of the sons of Manasseh according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Their region extended from Mahanaim, all Bashan, the entire kingdom
        of Og king of Bashan, and all the towns of Jair, which are in Bashan, sixty
        cities; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'also half of Gilead, with Ashtaroth and Edrei, the cities of the
        kingdom of Og in Bashan; these were for the sons of Machir the son of Manasseh,
        for half of the sons of Machir according to their families (clans).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'These are the territories which Moses distributed as an inheritance
        in the plains of Moab, beyond the Jordan at Jericho to the east. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: But to the tribe of Levi, Moses did not give an inheritance; the Lord,
        the God of Israel, is their inheritance, as He told them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Caleb\u2019s Request"
      title: "Caleb\u2019s Request"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the territories which the tribes of Israel inherited
        in the land of Canaan, which Eleazar the priest, and Joshua the son of Nun,
        and the heads of the households of the tribes of Israel apportioned to them
        as an inheritance, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'by the lot of their inheritance, as the Lord had commanded through
        Moses, for the nine tribes and the half-tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For Moses had given an inheritance to the two tribes and the half-tribe
        beyond the Jordan; but he did not give [any territory as] an inheritance
        to the Levites among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the sons of Joseph were two tribes, Manasseh and Ephraim, and
        no portion was given in the land to the Levites except cities in which to
        live, with their pasture lands for their livestock and for their property. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Israelites did just as the Lord had commanded Moses, and they
        divided the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the [tribe of the] sons of Judah approached Joshua in Gilgal,
        and Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite said to him, \u201CYou know
        the word which the Lord said to Moses the man of God concerning me and you
        in Kadesh-barnea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I was forty years old when Moses the servant of the Lord sent me
        from Kadesh-barnea to scout the land [of Canaan], and I brought a report
        back to him as it was in my heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My brothers (fellow spies) who went up with me made the heart of
        the people melt with fear; but I followed the Lord my God completely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Moses swore [an oath to me] on that day, saying, \u2018Be assured
        that the land on which your foot has walked will be an inheritance to you
        and to your children always, because you have followed the Lord my God completely.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now, look, the Lord has let me live, just as He said, these forty-five
        years since the Lord spoke this word to Moses, when Israel wandered in the
        wilderness; and now, look at me, I am eighty-five years old today. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I am still as strong today as I was the day Moses sent me; as my
        strength was then, so is my strength now, for war and for going out and coming
        in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So now, give me this hill country about which the Lord spoke that
        day, for you heard on that day that the [giant-like] Anakim were there, with
        great fortified cities; perhaps the Lord will be with me, and I shall drive
        them out just as the Lord said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Joshua blessed him and gave Hebron to Caleb the son of Jephunneh
        as an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore, Hebron became the inheritance of Caleb the son of Jephunneh
        the Kenizzite to this day, because he followed the Lord, the God of Israel,
        completely. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: The name of Hebron was formerly Kiriath-arba [city of Arba]; for Arba
        was the greatest man among the [giant-like] Anakim. Then the land had rest
        from war.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Territory of Judah'
      title: Territory of Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the lot (allotment) for the tribe of the sons of Judah according
        to their families reached [southward to] the border of Edom, southward to
        the wilderness of Zin at its most southern part. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their southern border was from the lower end of the Salt (Dead) Sea,
        from the bay that turns southward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then it proceeded southward to the ascent of Akrabbim and continued
        along to Zin, and then went by the south of Kadesh-barnea and continued along
        to Hezron, and went up to Addar and turned about to Karka. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It continued along to Azmon and proceeded to the Brook of Egypt (Wadi
        el-Arish), and the border ended at the [Mediterranean] sea. This was their
        southern border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The eastern border was the Salt (Dead) Sea, as far as the mouth of
        the Jordan. The northern border was from the bay of the sea at the mouth
        of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the border went up to Beth-hoglah, and continued along north
        of Beth-arabah, and the border went up to the [landmark of the] stone of
        Bohan the son of Reuben. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The border went up to Debir from the Valley of Achor, and turned
        northward toward Gilgal which is opposite the ascent of Adummim, which is
        on the south side of the valley; and the border continued on to the waters
        of En-shemesh and ended at En-rogel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the border went up by the Valley of Ben-hinnom (son of Hinnom)
        at the southern slope of the Jebusite [city] (that is, Jerusalem); and the
        border went up to the top of the mountain that lies before the Valley of
        Hinnom to the west, which is at the northern end of the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the border extended from the top of the mountain to the spring
        of the waters of Nephtoah and proceeded to the cities of Mount Ephron; then
        the border curved to Baalah (that is, Kiriath-jearim). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The border went around west from Baalah to Mount Seir, and passed
        along to the northern slope of Mount Jearim (that is, Chesalon), and went
        down to Beth-shemesh and then continued on through Timnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The border proceeded to the slope [of the hill] of Ekron northward,
        then curved to Shikkeron and continued to Mount Baalah and proceeded to Jabneel.
        Then the border ended at the [Mediterranean] sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The western border was at the Great Sea, with its coastline. This
        is the border around the tribe of the sons of Judah according to their families.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now to Caleb the son of Jephunneh Joshua gave a portion among the
        sons of Judah, as the Lord commanded him, namely, Kiriath-arba, Arba being
        the father of Anak (that is, Hebron). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Caleb drove out from there the three sons of Anak: Sheshai and
        Ahiman and Talmai, the children of Anak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then he went up from there against the people of Debir; Debir was
        formerly named Kiriath-sepher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Caleb said, \u201CI will give Achsah my daughter as wife to the man
        who attacks Kiriath-sepher and captures it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb\u2019s brother, captured it;
        so he gave him Achsah his daughter as a wife. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Now it came about that when Achsah came to Othniel, she persuaded
        him [to allow her] to ask her father for a field. Then she [rode up to Caleb
        and] dismounted from her donkey, and Caleb said to her, \u201CWhat do you
        want?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Achsah answered, \u201CGive me a blessing; since you have given me
        the [dry] land of the Negev (South country), give me springs of water, too.\u201D
        So he gave her the upper springs and the lower springs.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Judah according
        to their families (clans).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The cities of the tribe of the sons of Judah in the extreme south
        toward the border of Edom were Kabzeel and Eder and Jagur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and Kinah and Dimonah and Adadah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and Kedesh and Hazor and Ithnan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Ziph and Telem and Bealoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and Hazor-hadattah and Kerioth-hezron (that is, Hazor), '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Amam and Shema and Moladah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and Hazar-gaddah and Heshmon and Beth-pelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and Hazar-shual and Beersheba and Biziothiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Baalah and Iim and Ezem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'and Eltolad and Chesil and Hormah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and Ziklag and Madmannah and Sansannah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'and Lebaoth and Shilhim and Ain and Rimmon; in all twenty-nine cities
        with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'In the lowland: Eshtaol and Zorah and Ashnah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'and Zanoah and En-gannim, Tappuah and Enam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jarmuth and Adullam, Socoh and Azekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and Shaaraim and Adithaim and Gederah and Gederothaim; fourteen cities
        with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zenan and Hadashah and Migdal-gad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and Dilean and Mizpeh and Joktheel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Lachish and Bozkath and Eglon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'and Cabbon and Lahmas and Chitlish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'and Gederoth, Beth-dagon and Naamah and Makkedah; sixteen cities
        with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Libnah and Ether and Ashan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'and Iphtah and Ashnah and Nezib, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'and Keilah and Achzib and Mareshah; nine cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Ekron, with its towns and villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'from Ekron even to the sea, all that were beside Ashdod, with their
        villages;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Ashdod, with its towns and its villages; Gaza, with its towns and
        its villages; as far as the Brook of Egypt (Wadi el-Arish) and the Great
        [Mediterranean] Sea with its coastline.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'In the hill country: Shamir and Jattir and Socoh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'and Dannah and Kiriath-sannah (that is, Debir), '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'and Anab and Eshtemoh and Anim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'and Goshen and Holon and Giloh; eleven cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Arab and Dumah and Eshan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'and Janum and Beth-tappuah and Aphekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'and Humtah and Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron), and Zior; nine cities
        with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'Maon, Carmel and Ziph and Juttah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'and Jezreel and Jokdeam and Zanoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Kain, Gibeah and Timnah; ten cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Halhul, Beth-zur and Gedor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'and Maarath and Beth-anoth and Eltekon; six cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'Kiriath-baal (that is, Kiriath-jearim), and Rabbah; two cities with
        their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'In the wilderness [that slopes downward toward the Dead Sea]: Beth-arabah,
        Middin and Secacah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'and Nibshan and the City of Salt and Engedi; six cities with their
        villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: But as for the Jebusites, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the [tribe
        of the] sons of Judah were not able to drive them out; so the Jebusites live
        with the sons of Judah in Jerusalem to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Territory of Ephraim'
      title: Territory of Ephraim
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the lot (allotment) for the sons of Joseph went from the Jordan
        Valley at Jericho to the waters of Jericho on the east into the wilderness,
        going up from Jericho through the hill country to Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then it went from Bethel to Luz, and continued to Ataroth, the border
        of the Archites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It went down westward to the territory of the Japhletites, as far
        as the outskirts of lower Beth-horon, then to Gezer, and it ended at the
        sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Joseph, Manasseh and Ephraim, received their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now this was the territory of the sons of Ephraim according to their
        families: on the east side the border of their inheritance was Ataroth-addar,
        as far as upper Beth-horon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the border went westward at Michmethath on the north, and turned
        eastward to Taanath-shiloh and continued beyond it to the east of Janoah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'It went down from Janoah to Ataroth and to Naarah, touched Jericho
        and ended at the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The border continued from Tappuah westward to the Brook Kanah, and
        it ended at the [Mediterranean] sea. This is the inheritance of the tribe
        of the sons of Ephraim according to their families (clans), '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'with the cities which were set apart for the sons of Ephraim within
        the inheritance of the sons of Manasseh, all the cities with their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: But they did not drive out the Canaanites who lived in Gezer, so the
        Canaanites live among Ephraim to this day, and they became forced laborers.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Territory of Manasseh'
      title: Territory of Manasseh
      number: 1
      content: '  Now this was the lot (allotment) for the tribe of Manasseh, for
        he was the firstborn of Joseph. To Machir the firstborn of Manasseh, the
        father of Gilead, were allotted Gilead and Bashan, because he was a man of
        war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So the lot was also made for the rest of the sons of Manasseh according
        to their families\u2014for the sons of Abiezer and for the sons of Helek
        and for the sons of Asriel and for the sons of Shechem and for the sons of
        Hepher and for the sons of Shemida; these were the male descendants of Manasseh
        the son of Joseph according to their families (clans).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Zelophehad the son of Hepher, the son of Gilead, the son of Machir,
        the son of Manasseh, had no sons, only daughters; and these are the names
        of his daughters: Mahlah and Noah, Hoglah, Milcah and Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They came before Eleazar the priest and before Joshua the son of
        Nun and before the leaders and said, \u201CThe Lord commanded Moses to give
        us an inheritance among our brothers.\u201D So according to the command of
        the Lord Joshua gave them an inheritance among their father\u2019s brothers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So ten portions fell to Manasseh, besides the land of Gilead and
        Bashan, which is beyond the Jordan [on the east side of the river], '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'because the daughters of [Zelophehad, a descendant of] Manasseh had
        received an inheritance among his [other] sons [whose inheritance went to
        their male descendants]. The land of Gilead belonged to the rest of the sons
        of Manasseh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The territory of Manasseh reached from Asher to Michmethath which
        was east of Shechem; then the border went southward to the inhabitants of
        En-tappuah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The land of Tappuah belonged to Manasseh, but [the city of] Tappuah
        on the border of Manasseh belonged to the sons of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the border went down to the brook of Kanah, south of the brook
        (these cities belonged to Ephraim, among the cities of Manasseh), and Manasseh\u2019s
        border was on the north side of the brook and it ended at the sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The land on the south side belonged to Ephraim and that on the north
        side was Manasseh\u2019s, and the sea was their border; they reached to [the
        territory of] Asher on the north and to [the territory of] Issachar on the
        east. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Also, in Issachar and in Asher, Manasseh had Beth-shean and its towns
        and Ibleam and its towns, and the inhabitants of Dor and its towns, and the
        inhabitants of En-dor and its towns, and the inhabitants of Taanach and its
        towns, and the inhabitants of Megiddo and its towns; the third is Napheth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the sons of Manasseh were not able to [drive out the inhabitants
        and] take possession of these cities, because the Canaanites persisted in
        living in that land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When the Israelites became strong, they put the Canaanites to forced
        labor, but they did not drive them out completely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The sons of Joseph spoke to Joshua, saying, \u201CWhy have you given
        us only one lot and one portion as an inheritance, when we are a numerous
        people whom the Lord has so far blessed?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Joshua replied, \u201CIf you are a numerous people, go up to
        the forest and clear ground for yourselves there in the land of the Perizzites
        and the Rephaim, since the hill country of Ephraim is too narrow for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The sons of Joseph said, \u201CThe hill country is not enough for
        us, and all the Canaanites who live in the valley have iron chariots, both
        those who are in Beth-shean and its towns and those in the Valley of Jezreel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Joshua said to the house of Joseph, to Ephraim and to Manasseh, \u201CYou
        are a numerous people and have great power; you shall not have only one lot, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "but the hill country shall be yours. For though it is a forest, you
        shall clear it and possess it to its farthest borders; for you shall drive
        out the Canaanites, even though they have iron chariots and though they are
        strong.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rest of the Land Divided'
      title: Rest of the Land Divided
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the whole congregation of the Israelites assembled at Shiloh
        [in the tribal territory of Ephraim], and set up the Tent of Meeting there;
        and the land was subdued before them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There remained among the Israelites seven tribes who had not yet
        divided their inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Joshua asked them, \u201CHow long will you put off entering to
        take possession of the land which the Lord, the God of your fathers, has
        given you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Provide for yourselves three men from each tribe so that I may send
        them, and that they may go through the land and write a description of it
        with regard to their [tribal] inheritance; then they shall return to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They shall divide it into seven parts; [the tribe of] Judah shall
        remain in its territory on the south, and the house of Joseph shall remain
        in its territory on the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You shall describe the land in seven divisions, and bring the description
        here to me. I will cast lots for you here before the Lord our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the Levites have no portion among you, because the priesthood
        of the Lord is their inheritance. Gad and Reuben and half the tribe of Manasseh
        also have received their inheritance eastward beyond the Jordan, which Moses
        the servant of the Lord gave them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the men arose and went [on their way], and Joshua commanded those
        who went to describe the land, saying, \u201CGo and walk throughout the land
        and describe it, and return to me; and I will cast lots for you here before
        the Lord in Shiloh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the men set out and passed through the land, and described it
        by cities in seven divisions in a book; and they came back to Joshua to the
        camp at Shiloh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Territory of Benjamin'
      title: The Territory of Benjamin
      number: 10
      content: 'Joshua cast lots for them in Shiloh before the Lord, and there Joshua
        divided the land to the sons of Israel, [to each tribe] according to their
        portions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the lot (allotment) of the tribe of the sons of Benjamin came
        up according to their families, and the territory of their lot fell between
        [the tribes of] the sons of Judah and the sons of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On the north side their border began at the Jordan, then it went
        up the slope of Jericho on the north, and up through the hill country westward,
        and it ended at the Beth-aven wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the border continued southward toward Luz, to the slope of Luz
        (that is, Bethel); then the border went down to Ataroth-addar, by the hill
        that lies south of lower Beth-horon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The border changed course [from there] and turned around on the western
        side southward, from the hill that lies to the south opposite Beth-horon;
        it ended at Kiriath-baal (that is, Kiriath-jearim), a city of [the tribe
        of] the sons of Judah. This formed the western side [of Benjamin\u2019s territory]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The southern side was from the edge of Kiriath-jearim, and the border
        went on westward and went to the source of the waters of Nephtoah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the border went down to the edge of the hill overlooking the
        Valley of Ben-hinnom (son of Hinnom), which is at the north end of the Valley
        of Rephaim; and it descended to the Valley of Hinnom, south to the slope
        of the Jebusite, and went on down to En-rogel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then it turned toward the north and went on to En-shemesh and on
        to Geliloth, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim, and it went down to
        the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'It continued to the north to the side opposite [Beth-] Arabah and
        went down to the Arabah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The border continued along to the north of the slope of Beth-hoglah;
        and the border ended at the northern bay of the Salt (Dead) Sea, at the south
        end of the Jordan. This was the southern border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the Jordan River was its border on the east side. This was the
        inheritance of the sons of Benjamin, according to their families and according
        to its borders all around.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the cities of the tribe of the sons of Benjamin according to
        their families were Jericho and Beth-hoglah and Emek-keziz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and Beth-arabah and Zemaraim and Bethel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and Avvim and Parah and Ophrah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and Chephar-ammoni and Ophni and Geba; twelve cities with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Gibeon and Ramah and Beeroth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and Mizpeh and Chephirah and Mozah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and Rekem and Irpeel and Taralah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: and Zelah, Haeleph and the Jebusite (that is, Jerusalem), Gibeah,
        Kiriath; fourteen cities with their villages. This is the inheritance of
        [the tribe of] the sons of Benjamin according to their families (clans).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Territory of Simeon'
      title: Territory of Simeon
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the second lot fell to Simeon, to the tribe of the sons of
        Simeon according to their families (clans), and their inheritance was within
        the inheritance of the sons of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So they had as their inheritance Beersheba or Sheba and Moladah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and Hazar-shual and Balah and Ezem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Eltolad and Bethul and Hormah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Ziklag and Beth-marcaboth and Hazar-susah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and Beth-lebaoth and Sharuhen; thirteen cities with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Ain, Rimmon and Ether and Ashan; four cities with their villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and all the villages which were around these cities as far as Baalath-beer,
        Ramah of the Negev (South country). This was the inheritance of the tribe
        of the sons of Simeon according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Territory of Zebulun'
      title: Territory of Zebulun
      number: 9
      content: "The inheritance of the sons of Simeon was taken from the portion
        of the sons of Judah, for the share of the sons of Judah was too large for
        them; so the sons of Simeon received an inheritance within Judah\u2019s inheritance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The third lot came up for [the tribe of] the sons of Zebulun according
        to their families. The territory of their inheritance extended to Sarid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then its border went up westward and on to Maralah, and reached to
        Dabbesheth and reached to the brook east of Jokneam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then it turned from Sarid east toward the sunrise as far as the border
        of Chisloth-tabor, and it proceeded to Daberath and on up to Japhia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From there it continued east toward the sunrise to Gath-hepher and
        to Eth-kazin, and proceeded to Rimmon which turns toward Neah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The border circled it on the north to Hannathon, ending at the Valley
        of Iphtahel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Included were Kattah and Nahalal and Shimron and Idalah and Bethlehem;
        twelve cities with their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Territory of Issachar'
      title: Territory of Issachar
      number: 16
      content: 'This was the inheritance of the sons of Zebulun according to their
        families, these cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The fourth lot fell to [the tribe of] Issachar, to the sons of Issachar
        according to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Their territory included: Jezreel and Chesulloth and Shunem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and Hapharaim and Shion and Anaharath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and Rabbith and Kishion and Ebez, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and Remeth and En-gannim and En-haddah and Beth-pazzez. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The border reached to Tabor and Shahazumah and Beth-shemesh, and
        their border ended at the Jordan; sixteen cities with their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Territory of Asher'
      title: Territory of Asher
      number: 23
      content: 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Issachar according
        to their families, the cities and their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The fifth lot fell to the tribe of the sons of Asher according to
        their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their territory was Helkath and Hali and Beten and Achshaph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and Allammelech and Amad and Mishal; and on the west it reached to
        Carmel and to Shihor-libnath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then it turned eastward to Beth-dagon and reached Zebulun and the
        Valley of Iphtahel northward to Beth-emek and Neiel, and continued in the
        north to Cabul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and Ebron and Rehob and Hammon and Kanah, as far as Great Sidon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the border turned to Ramah, [reaching] to the fortified city
        of Tyre; and it turned to Hosah, and it ended at the [Mediterranean] sea
        at the region of Achzib. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Included were Ummah, and Aphek and Rehob; twenty-two cities with
        their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Territory of Naphtali'
      title: Territory of Naphtali
      number: 31
      content: 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Asher according
        to their families, these cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The sixth lot fell to [the tribe of] the sons of Naphtali according
        to their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Their border ran from Heleph, from the oak in Zaanannim and Adami-nekeb
        and Jabneel, as far as Lakkum, and it ended at the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then the border turned westward to Aznoth-tabor and went from there
        to Hukkok; and it reached Zebulun on the south and reached Asher on the west,
        and to Judah toward the east at the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The fortified cities were Ziddim, Zer, and Hammath, Rakkath and Chinnereth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and Adamah and Ramah and Hazor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and Kedesh and Edrei and En-hazor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and Yiron and Migdal-el, Horem and Beth-anath and Beth-shemesh; nineteen
        cities with their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: Territory of Dan'
      title: Territory of Dan
      number: 39
      content: 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Naphtali according
        to their families, the cities and their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The seventh lot fell to the tribe of the sons of Dan according to
        their families. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The territory of their inheritance included Zorah and Eshtaol and
        Ir-shemesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'and Shaalabbin and Aijalon and Ithlah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'and Elon and Timnah and Ekron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'and Eltekeh and Gibbethon and Baalath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'and Jehud and Bene-berak and Gath-rimmon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'and Me-jarkon and Rakkon, with the territory opposite Joppa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'The territory of the sons of Dan went beyond these; so the sons of
        Dan went up to fight against Leshem (Laish) and captured it. Then they struck
        it with the edge of the sword and took possession of it and settled there
        [between the tribes of Naphtali and Manasseh]; they renamed Leshem, Dan,
        after the name of their father (ancestor) Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the sons of Dan according
        to their families (clans), these cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'When they had finished dividing the land for inheritance by its borders,
        the Israelites gave an inheritance among them to Joshua the son of Nun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "According to the command of the Lord they gave him the city for which
        he asked\u2014Timnath-serah in the hill country of Ephraim. So he built the
        city and settled in it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: These are the inheritances which Eleazar the priest, Joshua the son
        of Nun, and the heads of the households of the tribes of the sons of Israel
        distributed by lot in Shiloh before the Lord at the doorway of the Tent of
        Meeting. So they finished dividing the land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Six Cities of Refuge'
      title: Six Cities of Refuge
      number: 1
      content: '  The Lord spoke to Joshua, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak to the Israelites, saying, \u2018Designate the cities
        of refuge (asylum), of which I spoke to you through Moses, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'so that the person (manslayer) who kills any person unintentionally,
        without premeditation, may flee there, and they shall be your refuge from
        the blood avenger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He shall flee to one of these cities, and shall stand at the entrance
        of the gate of the city and explain his case to the elders of that city;
        and they shall take him into [the protection of] the city and give him a
        place [to stay], so that he may live among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'If the blood avenger pursues him, they shall not hand the offender
        (manslayer) over to him, because he killed his neighbor unintentionally and
        without premeditation and did not hate him beforehand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He shall live in that city until he has stood before the congregation
        for judgment [and if acquitted of murder he must stay there], until the death
        of the one who is the high priest in those days. Then the offender (manslayer)
        shall return to his own city and his own house from which he fled.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they set apart and consecrated Kedesh in Galilee in the hill country
        of Naphtali, and Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and Kiriath-arba
        (that is, Hebron) in the hill country of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Beyond the Jordan east of Jericho, they designated Bezer in the wilderness
        on the plain from the tribe of Reuben, and Ramoth in Gilead from the tribe
        of Gad, and Golan in Bashan from the tribe of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: These were the appointed cities for all the Israelites and for the
        stranger sojourning (living temporarily) among them, so that whoever killed
        any person unintentionally may flee there, and not die by the hand of the
        blood avenger until he had stood before the congregation [for judgment].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Forty-eight Cities of the Levites'
      title: Forty-eight Cities of the Levites
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the heads of the households of the Levites came to Eleazar
        the priest, and Joshua the son of Nun, and the heads of the households of
        the tribes of the sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "They spoke to them at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, saying, \u201CThe
        Lord commanded Moses to give us cities to live in, with their pasture lands
        for our cattle.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So the sons of Israel gave the Levites from their inheritance these
        [forty-eight] cities and their pasture lands, in accordance with the command
        of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The [first] lot (allotment) came out for the families of the Kohathites.
        So those Levites who were sons (descendants) of Aaron the priest received
        thirteen cities by lot from the tribe of Judah and from the tribe of Simeon
        and from the tribe of Benjamin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The rest of the sons of Kohath received ten cities by lot from the
        families of the tribe of Ephraim and from the tribe of Dan and from the half-tribe
        of Manasseh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Gershon received thirteen cities by lot from the families
        of the tribe of Issachar and from the tribe of Asher and from the tribe of
        Naphtali and from the half-tribe of Manasseh in Bashan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Merari according to their families received twelve cities
        from the tribe of Reuben and from the tribe of Gad and from the tribe of
        Zebulun.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sons of Israel gave by lot to the Levites these cities with their
        pasture lands, as the Lord had commanded through Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They gave these cities which are mentioned here by name from the
        tribe of the sons of Judah and from the tribe of the sons of Simeon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and they were for the sons of Aaron, one of the families of the Kohathites,
        of the sons of Levi, because the lot fell to them first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They gave them [the city of] Kiriath-arba, Arba being the father
        of Anak (that is, Hebron) in the hill country of Judah, with its surrounding
        pasture lands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the fields of the city and its villages they had given to Caleb
        the son of Jephunneh as his property.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So to the sons of Aaron the priest they gave Hebron, the city of
        refuge for anyone who committed manslaughter, with its pasture lands, and
        Libnah with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and Jattir with its pasture lands and Eshtemoa with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and Holon with its pasture lands and Debir with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Ain with its pasture lands and Juttah with its pasture lands
        and Beth-shemesh with its pasture lands; nine cities from these two tribes
        (Judah and Simeon). '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'From the tribe of Benjamin, Gibeon with its pasture lands, and Geba
        with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Anathoth with its pasture lands and Almon with its pasture lands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'All the cities of the sons of Aaron, the priests, were thirteen cities
        with their pasture lands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the cities from the tribe of Ephraim were allotted to the families
        of the sons of Kohath, the Levites, even to the rest of the sons of Kohath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They gave them Shechem, the city of refuge for anyone who committed
        manslaughter, with its pasture lands, in the hill country of Ephraim, and
        Gezer with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and Kibzaim with its pasture lands and Beth-horon with its pasture
        lands; four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'From the tribe of Dan, Eltekeh with its pasture lands, Gibbethon
        with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Aijalon with its pasture lands, Gath-rimmon with its pasture lands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'From the half-tribe of Manasseh, they allotted Taanach with its pasture
        lands and Gath-rimmon with its pasture lands; two cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'All the cities with their pasture lands for the families of the rest
        of the sons of Kohath totaled ten.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'To the sons of Gershon, one of the families of the Levites, they
        gave from the other half-tribe of Manasseh, [the city of] Golan in Bashan,
        the city of refuge for anyone who committed manslaughter, with its pasture
        lands, and Be-eshterah with its pasture lands; two cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'From the tribe of Issachar, they gave Kishion with its pasture lands,
        Daberath with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Jarmuth with its pasture lands, and En-gannim with its pasture lands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'From the tribe of Asher, they gave Mishal with its pasture lands,
        Abdon with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Helkath with its pasture lands and Rehob with its pasture lands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'From the tribe of Naphtali, they gave Kedesh in Galilee, the city
        of refuge for anyone who committed manslaughter, with its pasture lands and
        Hammoth-dor with its pasture lands and Kartan with its pasture lands; three
        cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'All the cities of the Gershonites according to their families were
        thirteen cities with their pasture lands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'To the families of the sons of Merari, the rest of the Levites, they
        gave from the tribe of Zebulun, Jokneam with its pasture lands and Kartah
        with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Dimnah with its pasture lands and Nahalal with its pasture lands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'From the tribe of Reuben, they gave Bezer with its pasture lands
        and Jahaz with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Kedemoth with its pasture lands and Mephaath with its pasture lands;
        four cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'From the tribe of Gad, they gave Ramoth in Gilead, the city of refuge
        for anyone who committed manslaughter, with its pasture lands and Mahanaim
        with its pasture lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Heshbon with its pasture lands and Jazer with its pasture lands;
        four cities in all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'All [these were] the cities of the sons of Merari according to their
        families, the rest of the families of the Levites; and their lot was twelve
        cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'All the cities of the Levites in the midst of the property of the
        sons of Israel were forty-eight cities with their pasture lands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'These cities each had its surrounding pasture lands; so it was with
        all these cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So the Lord gave Israel all the land which He had sworn to give to
        their fathers (ancestors), and they took possession of it and lived in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The Lord gave them rest [from conflict] on every side, in accordance
        with everything that He had sworn to their fathers, and not one of all their
        enemies stood before them [in battle]; the Lord handed over all their enemies
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: Not one of the good promises which the Lord had spoken to the house
        of Israel failed; all had come to pass.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Tribes beyond Jordan Return'
      title: Tribes beyond Jordan Return
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Joshua called the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said to them, \u201CYou have kept all that Moses the servant
        of the Lord commanded you, and have listened to and obeyed my voice in everything
        that I commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You have not deserted your brothers these many days to this day,
        but have [carefully] kept the obligation of the commandment of the Lord your
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And now the Lord your God has given rest to your brothers, as He
        has promised them; so turn now and go to your tents, to the land of your
        possession, which Moses the servant of the Lord gave you beyond the [east
        side of the] Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Only be very careful and diligently observe the commandment and the
        law which Moses the servant of the Lord has commanded you to love the Lord
        your God and walk in all His ways and keep His commandments and hold fast
        to Him and serve Him with all your heart and with all your soul [your very
        life].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Joshua blessed them and sent them away, and they went to their
        tents.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now to the one-half of the tribe of Manasseh Moses had given a possession
        in Bashan, but to the other half Joshua gave a possession on the west side
        of the Jordan among their brothers. So when Joshua sent them away to their
        tents, he blessed them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and he said to them, \u201CReturn to your tents with great riches
        and with very much livestock, with silver, gold, bronze, iron, and with very
        many clothes; divide the spoil of your enemies with your brothers (fellow
        tribesmen).\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Offensive Altar'
      title: The Offensive Altar
      number: 9
      content: 'So the sons (descendants) of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh returned home and departed from the [other] sons (western tribes)
        of Israel at Shiloh which is in the land of Canaan, to go to the land of
        Gilead, to the land of their own which they had possessed, in accordance
        with the command of the Lord through Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When they came to the region of the Jordan which is in the land of
        Canaan, the sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh
        built an altar there by the Jordan, an altar that was great to behold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the [other] sons of Israel heard it said, \u201CLook, the sons
        of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh have built an
        altar at the edge of the land of Canaan, in the region [west] of the Jordan,
        on the side belonging to the sons of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When the sons of Israel heard of it, the whole congregation of the
        Israelites gathered at Shiloh to make war against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the sons of Israel sent Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest
        to the sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh,
        in the land of Gilead, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and with him ten leaders, one leader from each father\u2019s household
        from each of the tribes of Israel; and each one was the head of his father\u2019s
        household among the thousands of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They came to the sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh, in the land of Gilead, and they said to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis is what the entire congregation of the Lord says, \u2018What
        is this disloyal and unfaithful act which you have committed against the
        God of Israel, so as to turn away from following the Lord this day, by building
        yourselves an altar, to rebel against the Lord this day? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Is the wrongdoing (idolatry) of Peor not enough for us, from which
        we have not cleansed ourselves to this day, even though the affliction [in
        which twenty-four thousand died] came on the congregation of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'that you would turn away this day from following the Lord? If you
        rebel against the Lord today, He will be angry with the entire congregation
        of Israel tomorrow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "If, however, the land of your possession is unclean, then cross into
        the land of the possession of the Lord, where the Lord\u2019s tabernacle
        is situated, and settle down among us. But do not rebel against the Lord,
        or rebel against us by building an altar for yourselves, besides the altar
        of the Lord our God [at Shiloh]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Did not Achan the son of Zerah act unfaithfully in the things under
        the ban, and [as a result God\u2019s] wrath came on the entire congregation
        of Israel? And that man did not perish alone in his wrongdoing.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the half-tribe of
        Manasseh answered and said to the heads of the families of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThe Mighty One, God, the Lord, the Mighty One, God, the Lord!
        He knows, and may Israel itself know. If it was in rebellion, or if in an
        unfaithful act against the Lord, do not save us this day! "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If we have built an altar for ourselves to turn away from following
        the Lord, or if [we did so] to offer a burnt offering or grain offering on
        it, or if to offer sacrifices of peace offerings on it, may the Lord Himself
        require it [of us and hold us responsible]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But in truth we have done this out of concern, for a reason, saying,
        \u2018In time to come your sons (descendants) may say to our sons, \u201CWhat
        claim do you have to the Lord, the God of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For the Lord has made the Jordan a border between us and you, you
        sons of Reuben and sons of Gad; you have no part in the Lord.\u201D So your
        sons (descendants) may cause our sons to stop fearing the Lord.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CSo we said, \u2018Let us prepare and build an altar, not for
        burnt offering or for sacrifice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "but to be a witness between us and you and between the generations
        after us, that we are to perform the service of the Lord before Him with
        our burnt offerings, and with our sacrifices and with our peace offerings,
        so that your sons (descendants) will not say to our sons in time to come,
        \u201CYou have no part in the Lord.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So we said, \u2018If your descendants should say this to us or to
        our descendants in time to come, then we can reply, \u201CSee the copy of
        the altar of the Lord which our fathers made, not for burnt offering or for
        sacrifice, but rather it is a witness between us and you.\u201D\u2009\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Far be it from us that we should rebel against the Lord and turn
        away from following the Lord this day, by building an altar for burnt offering,
        for grain offering or for sacrifice, besides the altar of the Lord our God
        which is before His tabernacle [in Shiloh].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So when Phinehas the priest and the leaders of the congregation and
        heads of the families of Israel who were with him, heard the words which
        the sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the sons of Manasseh spoke, it
        pleased them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest said to the sons of Reuben
        and the sons of Gad and the sons of Manasseh, \u201CToday we know that the
        Lord is among us, because you have not committed this unfaithful act against
        the Lord; indeed you have saved Israel from the hand of the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest and the leaders returned
        from the sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad, from the land of Gilead to the
        land of Canaan, to the sons of Israel, and brought back word to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The report pleased the sons of Israel, and the sons of Israel blessed
        God; and they said no more about going to battle against them to destroy
        the land in which the sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad were living. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "The sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad called the altar Witness;
        \u201CFor it is a witness between us that the Lord is God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joshua\u2019s Farewell Address"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Farewell Address"
      number: 1
      content: '  A long time after that, when the Lord had given Israel rest from
        all their enemies on every side, and Joshua had grown old and advanced in
        years, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "that Joshua called all Israel, their elders and their heads and their
        judges and their officers, and said to them, \u201CI am old and advanced
        in years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you have seen all that the Lord your God has done to all these
        nations for your sake; for the Lord your God is He who has been fighting
        for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'See, I have allotted to you these nations that remain as an inheritance
        for your tribes, with all the nations which I have cut off, from the Jordan
        [on the east] to the Great [Mediterranean] Sea toward the setting sun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord your God will push them away from before you and drive them
        out of your sight and you will take possession of their land, just as the
        Lord your God promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Be steadfast and very determined to keep and to do everything that
        is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, so that you do not turn aside
        from it to the right or the left, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'so that you do not associate with these nations which remain among
        you, or mention the name of their gods, or make anyone swear [an oath by
        them], or serve them, or bow down to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But you are to cling to the Lord your God, just as you have done
        to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the Lord has driven out great and mighty nations from before
        you; and as for you, no man has been able to stand [in opposition] before
        you to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'One of your men puts to flight a thousand, for the Lord your God
        is He who is fighting for you, just as He promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So be very careful and watchful of yourselves to love the Lord your
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For if you ever turn back and cling to the rest of these nations,
        these that are left among you, and intermarry with them, so that you associate
        with them and they with you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'know and understand with certainty that the Lord your God will not
        continue to drive these nations out from before you; but they will be a snare
        and trap to you, and a whip on your sides and thorns in your eyes, until
        you perish from this good land which the Lord your God has given you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CNow behold, today I am going the way of all the earth, and
        you know in all your hearts and in all your souls that not one word of all
        the good words which the Lord your God has promised concerning you has failed;
        all have been fulfilled for you, not one of them has failed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'It shall come about that just as every good word which the Lord your
        God spoke and promised to you has been fulfilled for you, so the Lord will
        bring upon you every bad thing [about which He warned you], until He has
        destroyed and eliminated you from this good land which the Lord your God
        has given you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When you transgress (violate) the covenant of the Lord your God,
        which He commanded you [to follow], and you go and serve other gods and bow
        down to them, then the anger of the Lord will be kindled against you, and
        you shall perish quickly from the good land which He has given you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joshua Reviews Israel\u2019s History"
      title: "Joshua Reviews Israel\u2019s History"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel to Shechem, and called
        for the elders of Israel and for their heads and for their judges and for
        their officers; they presented themselves before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Joshua said to all the people, \u201CThis is what the Lord, the God
        of Israel, says, \u2018Your fathers, including Terah, the father of Abraham
        and the father of Nahor, lived beyond the [Euphrates] River in ancient times;
        and they served other gods. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I took your father Abraham from beyond the [Euphrates] River
        and led him through all the land of Canaan, and multiplied his descendants,
        and I gave him Isaac. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'To Isaac I gave Jacob and Esau, and to Esau I gave [the hill country
        of] Mount Seir to possess; but Jacob and his sons went down to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then I sent Moses and Aaron, and I plagued Egypt by what I did in
        its midst; and afterward I brought you out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then I brought your fathers out of Egypt, and you came to the sea;
        and the Egyptians pursued your fathers with chariots and horsemen to the
        Red Sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When they cried out to the Lord [for help], He put darkness between
        you and the Egyptians, and brought the sea upon them and covered them; and
        your own eyes saw what I did in Egypt. And you lived in the wilderness a
        long time (forty years). '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then I brought you into the land of the Amorites who lived on the
        other side of the Jordan, and they fought with you; and I gave them into
        your hand, and you took possession of their land and I destroyed them before
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, arose and fought against
        Israel, and he sent and called Balaam the son of Beor to curse you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But I would not listen to Balaam. Therefore he had to bless you,
        so I saved you from Balak\u2019s hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You crossed the Jordan and came to Jericho; and the citizens of Jericho
        fought against you, as did the Amorite and the Perizzite and the Canaanite
        and the Hittite and the Girgashite, the Hivite and the Jebusite; and so I
        gave them into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I sent the hornet [that is, the terror of you] before you, which
        drove the two kings of the Amorites out before you; but it was not by your
        sword or by your bow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I gave you a land for which you did not labor, and cities which you
        did not build, and you live in them; you eat from vineyards and olive groves
        which you did not plant.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CNow, therefore, fear the Lord and serve Him in sincerity and
        in truth; remove the gods which your fathers served on the other side of
        the [Euphrates] River and in Egypt, and serve the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "If it is unacceptable in your sight to serve the Lord, choose for
        yourselves this day whom you will serve: whether the gods which your fathers
        served that were on the other side of the River, or the gods of the Amorites
        in whose land you live; but as for me and my house, we will serve the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The people answered, \u201CFar be it from us to abandon (reject)
        the Lord to serve other gods; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for the Lord our God is He who brought us and our fathers up out
        of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage, and who did these great
        signs (miracles) in our sight and kept us safe all along the way that we
        went and among all the peoples among whom we passed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The Lord drove all the peoples out from before us, even the Amorites
        who lived in the land. We also will serve the Lord, for He is our God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Joshua said to the people, \u201CYou will not be able to serve
        the Lord [if you serve any other gods], for He is a holy God; He is a jealous
        God [demanding what is rightfully and uniquely His]. He will not forgive
        your transgression [of His law] or your sins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "If you do abandon (reject) the Lord and serve foreign gods, then
        He will turn and do you harm and consume and destroy you after He has done
        you good.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The people said to Joshua, \u201CNo, but we will serve [only] the
        Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Joshua then said to the people, \u201CYou are witnesses against yourselves
        that you have chosen for yourselves the Lord, to serve Him.\u201D And they
        said, \u201CWe are witnesses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CNow then, remove the foreign gods which are among you, and
        incline your hearts toward the Lord, the God of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The people said to Joshua, \u201CWe will serve the Lord our God and
        we will listen to and obey His voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So Joshua made a covenant with the people that day, and made for
        them a statute and an ordinance at Shechem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Joshua wrote these words in the Book of the Law of God. Then
        he took a large stone and set it up there under the oak that was in [the
        courtyard of] the sanctuary of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Joshua then said to all the people, \u201CLook, this stone shall
        serve as a witness against us, for it has heard all the words of the Lord
        which He spoke to us; so it shall be a witness against you, so that [afterward]
        you do not deny your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Joshua\u2019s Death and Burial"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Death and Burial"
      number: 28
      content: 'Then Joshua sent the people away, each to [the territory of] his
        inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'It happened after these things that Joshua the son of Nun, the servant
        of the Lord, died, at the age of a hundred and ten years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'They buried him in the territory of his inheritance in Timnath-serah,
        which is in the hill country of Ephraim, on the north side of Mount Gaash.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Israel served the Lord all the days of Joshua and all the days of
        the elders who outlived Joshua, and had known all the works of the Lord which
        He had done for Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now they buried the bones of Joseph, which the children of Israel
        brought up from Egypt, at Shechem, in the plot of land which Jacob had bought
        from the sons of Hamor the father of Shechem for a hundred pieces of money;
        and it became the inheritance of the sons of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: And Eleazar [the priest], the son of Aaron died; and they buried him
        at Gibeah [on the hill] of Phinehas his son, which had been given to him
        in the hill country of Ephraim.
      comments: []
